Sentencas: The effects of pore formers added into the extrusion slurry of anode support microtubes on the mechanical and electrochemical performance of the microtubes are investigated in this study.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For this purpose, several microtubular anode supports are fabricated by using various pore formers with different particle sizes.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of pore former content is also taken into consideration for a certain pore former type.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The flexural strengths of the anode support microtubes are measured via three point bending tests and reliability analysis is performed.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The porosities of the anode supports are also determined along with microstructural investigations.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results reveal that the flexural strength decreases with increasing the particle size of the pore former employed for a fixed pore former content and with increasing the pore former content for a certain pore former material considered.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, a number microtubular cells are fabricated based on the various microtubular anode supports and their electrochemical performances are evaluated via performance and impedance tests.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The impedance results indicate that the cell performance is mainly restricted by the diffusion polarization.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among the pore former materials considered in this study, the highest cell performance for a certain pore former content of 20 vol% is measured from the cell prepared with graphite (325 mesh) pore former at all temperatures and hydrogen flowrates studied.
Titulo: Effects of pore former type on mechanical and electrochemical performance of anode support microtubes in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The optimization studies display that the cell performance can be further improved by increasing the pore former content to 22.5 vol% for this pore former material.(c) 2022 Hydrogen Energy Publications LLC.
